This paper proposes a novel neural-network-based model for uncertainty measurement in text classification tasks, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a metric learning method on feature representations, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses real-world data sets and experiments with neural networks, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
